SimpleType.name: Modelon.ThermoFluid.Choices.ChannelThermalOpt
SimpleType.description: Choice of which thermal variable to prescribe for sizing

Item.name: Q_flow
Item.description: Heat flow rate, Q_flow0

Item.name: T_out
Item.description: Outlet temperature, T_out0

Item.name: never
Item.description: Do not use as state at all.

Item.name: avoid
Item.description: Use as state, if it cannot be avoided (but only if variable appears differentiated and no other potential state with attribute default, prefer, or always can be selected).

Item.name: default
Item.description: Use as state if appropriate, but only if variable appears differentiated.

Item.name: prefer
Item.description: Prefer it as state over those having the default value (also variables can be selected, which do not appear differentiated).

Item.name: always
Item.description: Do use it as a state.

SimpleType.name: Modelica.Blocks.Types.Smoothness
SimpleType.description: Enumeration defining the smoothness of table interpolation

Item.name: LinearSegments
Item.description: Linear interpolation of table points

Item.name: ContinuousDerivative
Item.description: Akima spline interpolation of table points (such that the first derivative is continuous)

Item.name: ConstantSegments
Item.description: Piecewise constant interpolation of table points (the value from the previous abscissa point is returned)

Item.name: MonotoneContinuousDerivative1
Item.description: Fritsch-Butland spline interpolation (such that the monotonicity is preserved and the first derivative is continuous)

Item.name: MonotoneContinuousDerivative2
Item.description: Steffen spline interpolation of table points (such that the monotonicity is preserved and the first derivative is continuous)

Item.name: ModifiedContinuousDerivative
Item.description: Modified Akima spline interpolation of table points (such that the first derivative is continuous and shortcomings of the original Akima method are avoided)

SimpleType.name: Modelica.Blocks.Types.Extrapolation
SimpleType.description: Enumeration defining the extrapolation of table interpolation

Item.name: HoldLastPoint
Item.description: Hold the first/last table point outside of the table scope

Item.name: LastTwoPoints
Item.description: Extrapolate by using the derivative at the first/last table points outside of the table scope

Item.name: Periodic
Item.description: Repeat the table scope periodically

Item.name: NoExtrapolation
Item.description: Extrapolation triggers an error

SimpleType.name: Modelica.Blocks.Types.TimeEvents
SimpleType.description: Enumeration defining the time event handling of time table interpolation

Item.name: Always
Item.description: Always generate time events at interval boundaries

Item.name: AtDiscontinuities
Item.description: Generate time events at discontinuities (defined by duplicated sample points)

Item.name: NoTimeEvents
Item.description: No time events at interval boundaries

SimpleType.name: Modelon.Types.FaultAction
SimpleType.description: Enumeration defining the action to take when a fault is detected

Item.name: Error
Item.description: Abort the simulation with an error

Item.name: Terminate
Item.description: Terminate the simulation without error

Item.name: Warning
Item.description: Print a warning and continue simulation

Item.name: Nothing
Item.description: Continue simulation without any action

SimpleType.name: Modelon.Media.Interfaces.Types.ReferenceEnthalpy
SimpleType.description: Enumeration defining the reference enthalpy of a medium

Item.name: ZeroAt0K
Item.description: The enthalpy is 0 at 0 K (default), if the enthalpy of formation is excluded

Item.name: ZeroAt25C
Item.description: The enthalpy is 0 at 25 degC, if the enthalpy of formation is excluded

Item.name: UserDefined
Item.description: The user-defined reference enthalpy is used at 298.15 K (25 degC)

Item.name: ConstantDensity
Item.description: The density is a constant

Item.name: TemperatureDependent
Item.description: The density is a function of temperature

Item.name: PressureDependent
Item.description: The density is a function of pressure

Item.name: FullyCompressible
Item.description: The density is a function of the full thermodynamic state
